Sentece: The pharmacokinetic parameters derived for pancuronium were in the range of previously reported values, except that the mean total systemic plasma clearance (0.79 +/- 0.28 ml X min-1 X kg-1) was reduced and the mean terminal phase half-life (169 min) was longer in these patients.

Sentece: An analysis using the Hill equation of the Cp-response relationship, during and after the constant-rate infusion of pancuronium bromide, resulted in effective plasma concentrations for 50% paralysis ( ECp50 ) of 0.35 +/- 0.06 micrograms X ml-1 and 0.20 +/- 0.09 micrograms X ml-1, respectively, for mechanical twitch response.
